<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Scrabble vs Words With Friends — Key Differences Explained</h1>

<p>Scrabble and Words With Friends look nearly identical at first glance — both are crossword-style word games on a grid with premium squares. But the differences in board layout, scoring, tile distribution, and dictionaries create surprisingly distinct strategic experiences. A top Scrabble player won't automatically dominate in WWF, and vice versa.</p>

<!-- Stat Strip -->
<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
  <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-center">
    <div><span class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1948</span><br><span class="text-sm text-gray-400">Scrabble created</span></div>
    <div><span class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2009</span><br><span class="text-sm text-gray-400">WWF launched</span></div>
    <div><span class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15×15</span><br><span class="text-sm text-gray-400">both use same grid</span></div>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Board Layout Differences</h2>

<p>Both games use a 15×15 grid, but the placement of premium squares is completely different. This fundamentally changes opening strategy and board control:</p>

<table class="w-full text-sm my-4">
  <thead><tr class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800"><th class="p-2 text-left">Feature</th><th class="p-2 text-left">Scrabble</th><th class="p-2 text-left">Words With Friends</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="p-2">Centre square</td><td class="p-2">Double Word Score (★)</td><td class="p-2">No bonus (plain)</td></tr>
    <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="p-2">Triple Word squares</td><td class="p-2">8 (corners + edges)</td><td class="p-2">8 (different positions)</td></tr>
    <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="p-2">Triple Letter squares</td><td class="p-2">12</td><td class="p-2">12 (repositioned)</td></tr>
    <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="p-2">Premium symmetry</td><td class="p-2">Rotational + diagonal</td><td class="p-2">Rotational only</td></tr>
    <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="p-2">Opening word bonus</td><td class="p-2">×2 (DWS on centre)</td><td class="p-2">×1 (no bonus on centre)</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
  <p class="text-sm text-purple-300"><strong class="text-purple-400">Key Impact:</strong> The absence of a centre DWS in WWF means opening words score roughly half what they would in Scrabble. This makes going first less of an advantage in WWF.</p>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Scoring Differences</h2>

<p>Individual tile values differ between the two games. Some letters are worth more in WWF, others less:</p>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
    <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-400 mb-2">Worth MORE in WWF</h3>
    <ul class="text-sm text-gray-300 list-disc pl-4 space-y-1">
      <li>J: 10 pts (vs 8 in Scrabble)</li>
      <li>X: 8 pts (same)</li>
      <li>Z: 10 pts (same)</li>
      <li>H: 4 pts (vs 4, same)</li>
      <li>D: 2 pts (same)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/10">
    <h3 class="font-semibold text-blue-400 mb-2">Worth LESS in WWF</h3>
    <ul class="text-sm text-gray-300 list-disc pl-4 space-y-1">
      <li>Q: 10 pts (same, but fewer valid Q words)</li>
      <li>K: 5 pts (same)</li>
      <li>Overall: WWF scores tend slightly lower per game</li>
      <li>Bingo bonus: 35 pts in WWF (vs 50 in Scrabble)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Dictionary Differences</h2>

<p>This is the biggest difference for serious players. The dictionaries are entirely different word lists:</p>

<table class="w-full text-sm my-4">
  <thead><tr class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800"><th class="p-2 text-left">Aspect</th><th class="p-2 text-left">Scrabble</th><th class="p-2 text-left">Words With Friends</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="p-2">Dictionary used</td><td class="p-2">SOWPODS (international) or TWL (North America)</td><td class="p-2">ENABLE + custom additions</td></tr>
    <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="p-2">Total words</td><td class="p-2">~280,000 (SOWPODS)</td><td class="p-2">~173,000 (ENABLE)</td></tr>
    <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="p-2">Offensive words</td><td class="p-2">Included in SOWPODS, removed from tournament play in some regions</td><td class="p-2">Many removed</td></tr>
    <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="p-2">Updates</td><td class="p-2">Every few years (Collins/Hasbro)</td><td class="p-2">Irregular additions by Zynga</td></tr>
    <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="p-2">Notable exclusions</td><td class="p-2">Few — very permissive</td><td class="p-2">Many valid Scrabble words rejected</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
  <p class="text-sm text-purple-300"><strong class="text-purple-400">Practical Impact:</strong> Words like QI, ZA, and XI are valid in Scrabble but some may not be accepted in WWF. Always check the specific dictionary if switching between games.</p>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Tile Distribution Comparison</h2>

<p>The number of each letter in the tile bag differs slightly between games:</p>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
