  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
    <h3 class="font-semibold text-purple-400 mb-2">WWF (104 tiles)</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">E×13, A×9, I×8, O×8, N×5, R×6, T×7 — slightly different distribution with 2 blanks</p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Strategic Implications</h2>

<p>The combined differences mean strategy that works in one game doesn't always transfer:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Bingo value</strong> — 50 points in Scrabble vs 35 in WWF. Fishing for bingos is more rewarding in Scrabble</li>
  <li><strong>Opening play</strong> — less valuable in WWF (no centre DWS), so going second isn't as disadvantaged</li>
  <li><strong>Short words</strong> — some 2-letter words valid in Scrabble don't work in WWF. Parallel plays may fail</li>
  <li><strong>Premium square access</strong> — different positions mean memorised TWS approaches from Scrabble won't apply</li>
  <li><strong>Challenges</strong> — Scrabble has a penalty for wrong challenges; WWF simply rejects invalid words with no penalty</li>
  <li><strong>Tile swapping</strong> — WWF allows swap + play; Scrabble requires forfeiting your turn</li>
</ul>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-3">
